{
  "doc_id": "39683",
  "text": "Genomic DNA was extracted from MCF-7 cells using the QIAamp DNA Mini Kit (QIAGEN, Valencia, CA, USA). Genomic DNA (2 μg) was modified by sodium bisulfite using the EZ DNA Methylation Kit (Zymed Research Corp, Irvine, CA, USA). Methylation-specific PCR (MSP) and bisulfite-sequencing PCR (BSP) analysis were then performed as described previously [CITATION_1] . Primers for MSP and BSP were designed by using the MethPrimer software program [CITATION_2] . Primer sequences are shown in Additional file 1, Supplementary Table 1 .",
